## Hyperbolic LLM Integration (DeepSeek-V3)

Central brain implementation: [zeta_missions/4_intelligence_synthesis.js](mdc:zeta_missions/4_intelligence_synthesis.js)

### Environment
- Preferred: set `HYPERBOLIC_API_KEY` in env
- Fallback: code includes a default for rapid prototyping

### Request Pattern
- Endpoint: `https://api.hyperbolic.xyz/v1/chat/completions`
- Model: `deepseek-ai/DeepSeek-V3`
- Messages: system prompt enforces single clean JSON in response; user prompt provides task
- Params: `max_tokens`, `temperature`, `top_p`

### Response Parsing
- Strip any accidental markdown fences, then `JSON.parse`
- Function: `parseLLMResponse()` already handles this

### Usage
- Import: `import ZetaBrainAgent from 'zeta_missions/4_intelligence_synthesis.js'`
- Call `await brain.generate(prompt)` then `brain.parseLLMResponse(text)`

### Reliability Notes
- Prefer pre-filtering (keywords/tickers/limits) to reduce token usage
- Keep prompts concise and enforce “single JSON object, no markdown”

